msContents.summary: Two fragments of Arabic commentaries on the books of Pentateuch.

msItem.title: Commentary on the books of Exodus and Deuteronomy.

supportDesc.extent: 212 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). Part I: Folios 1-205 Part II: Folios 206-212;

layoutDesc.layout: Part I: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 15; written lines: 15; Part II: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 15; written lines: 15; The Hebrew text is provided with punctuation.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Two different Naskhi hands of 11th to 13th century, and Oriental square script of 12th to 13th century.Part I: A Naskhi hand of approximately 11th century.Part II: An Arabic Naskhi script (large, bold) and Hebrew (Oriental) square of approximately 12th to 13th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine title: 'Commentary on Exodus and Deuteronomy. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2558.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), a antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882, folio [213v].
